HYPER TEXT MARKUP LANGUAGE AND CASCADING STYLE SHEET:-
========================================================
WHAT IS HTML?
==================
-->html stands for hyper text markup language.
-->html is the standard markup langauage for creating layout(structures) for web pages.
-->html describes the structure of a web page.
-->html consists  of a series of elements.
-->html elements tell the browser how to display the content.
-->html files are saved with ".hmtl" or ".htm" extension.
-->html is not an case sensitive lanaguage.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BASIC STRUCUTURE OF HTML:-
===========================
<!DOCTYPE HTML>
   <html>
         <head>
               <meta></meta>
               <title>This is My New Web Page</title>
         </head>
         <body>
             <h1> my first heading </h1>
             <p>  my first Paragraph <br> happy to start my new lesrning html </p>
         </body>
   </hmtl>
-->The "<!DOCTYPE HTML>" declaration defines that the document is a html5 document.
-->The "<html>" element is the root element of an html page.
-->The "<head>" element contains about the meta information of a html page or web page.
-->The "<title>"element specifies a title for the html page.
-->The "<body>" element defines the document's body and is a container for all the visible contents such as headings, paragraphs, hyper links, images, tables , etc..
-->The "<h1>" element defines a larger heading.
-->The "<h1> to <h6>" defines HTML headings.
-->The "<p>" element defines a paragraph.
-->The "<br>"element is used to break the line and it is also known as empty element.
-->"<p style="color:red">  whenever we add extra properties to the html tags such properties are called attributes.
=================================================================================================================================================================================================================
ATTRIBUTES:-
=====================
-->All HTML elements have attributes.
-->Attributes provide additional information about elements.
-->Attributes are always specifies in a start tag.
-->Attributes usually come in name/value pairs like : name="value".
-->The <a> tag defines a hyper Link. 
     -->The href attribute specifies the url of the page the link goes to.
    Ex:- <a href="https://acet.ac.in/"> Visit Link </a>
-->The <img> tag is used to embed an image in the html page. 
     -->The src attribute specifies the path to the image to be dipalyed.
     -->The <img> tag also contains width and height attributes which specifies the width and height of the image.
    EX:- <img src="img.jpg" height=500 width=500>
  -->There are two ways to specify the  url in src attribute, they are:
       Absolute URL:- Links to an external image that is hosted on the another website.
         Ex:- <img src="https://www.w3schools.com/images/img_girl.jpg">
       Relative URL:- Links to an image that is hosted within the website.
         Ex:- <img src="image.jpg">
 -->The "alt" attribute for the "img" tag specifies the alternative text for the image incase of error in loading image due to poor Network Connection ,
    user can understand easily by seeing the alternative text.
       Ex:-  <img src="image.jpg" alt="This is Ajay Picture">
-->The Style attribute specifies different styles to an element such as color , font - size and more..        
     Ex:- <p color:"blue">This is a paragraph </p>
-->The "Lang" attribute of html page declares the language of the html page.
-->The HTML Standard does not require qoutes to the attribute values but the w3c recommends quotes to the attribute values.
=================================================================================================================================================================
LET US SEE ELEMENTS IN THE HEAD TAG:-
======================================
-->It's a Container for metadata. Metadata typically defines the document's title, character set, styles, scripts and other meta information.
-->"<title>" -->title of Document.
-->"<style>" -->internal css styles.
-->"<base>" -->Specifies the base URL for all relative URL's in a Document.
-->"<meta>" -->is used to specify page description, keywords, author of Document , last modified charset and other metadata.
-->"<link>" -->defines the link between a Document and an external resource.
HTML HEADINGS:-
====================
-->They are defined with the <h1> to <h6>. <h1> defines the most important heading and <h6> defines the least important heading.it is important to use headings to show the document structure.
   Ex:-  <h1>Heading 1</h1>
         <h2>Heading 2</h2>
         <h3>Heading 3</h3>
         <h4>Heading 4</h4>
         <h5>Heading 5</h5>
         <h6>Heading 6</h6>
-->Each HTML Heading have default Size. however you can specify the size for any heading with the style attribute using the css "font-size" property.
          <h1 "font-size:60px;">Heading 1</h1>
--> The <hr> tag defines the horizontal bar or horizontal line.

HTML PARAGRAPH AND FROMATTING:-
==========================
-->It defines a paragraph.it is written as "<p>HELLO</p>". 
-->"<br>" element defines a line break.
-->"<pre>" element defines a preformatted text.
-->The text inside a "<pre>" element is displayed in a fixed-width font.

Formatting:-
===========
-->"<b>" -- Bold text
-->"<strong>" -- important text.
-->"<em>" -- ephasized text.
-->"<i>" --italic text
-->"<small>" -- small text
-->"<mark>"  --marked text
-->"<sub>" --- subscript text
-->"<sup>" --- superscript text
-->"<del>" --- deleted text
-->"<ins>" --- inserted text
==============================================================================================================================================================================================
HTML STYLES:-
=============
-->   The HTML style attribute is used to add styles to an element such as color,font , size and more.
--> syntax:
      <tagname style="property:value;">
-->  The property is a CSS property and the value is a CSS value.
-->  The CSS "background-color" property defines the background color of an html element.
       Eg:- <body style="background-color:red;"></body>
-->  The CSS "color" property defines the text color for an HTML element.
        Eg:<p style="color:red;"></p>
-->  The CSS "font-size" property defines the text size for an HTML element.
         Eg:- <p style="font-size:160%;"></p> 
-->  The CSS "text-align" property defines the horizontal text- alignment  for an HTML element.
         Eg:- <p style="text-align:center";> </p>
==================================================================================================================================================================
HTML QUOATATIONS:-
===================
-->The HTML "<q>" tag defines a short quoatation.
    Eg:- <p>WWF's goal is to: <q>Build a future where people live in harmony with nature.</q></p>
-->The HTML "<abbr>" tag defines an abbrevation.
    Eg:- <p>The <abbr title="World Health Organization">WHO</abbr> was founded in 1948.</p>
-->The HTML "<address>" tag defines the contact information for the author of an article.
    Eg:- <address>
Written by John Doe.<br>
Visit us at:<br>
Example.com<br>
Box 564, Disneyland<br>
USA
</address>
